commit.message:
fix(anthropic): preserve the error code returned by model (#13256)

## Background

#12203 

when a provider-executed tool errors, the structured data containing the
error code is lost when this flows through toUIMessageStream.

the onError callback converts it into a generic string. on the next
request when trying to convert the error code, it falls back to
`unknown`, and Anthropic rejects it with a 400 because `unknown` isn't a
valid error code

## Summary

- serialize the error directly: strings pass through, objects get
stringify'd
- change the fallback error code from `unknown` to `unavailable`

## Manual Verification

verfied by running the following repro:

<details>
<summary>repro</summary>

```ts
import { anthropic } from '@ai-sdk/anthropic';
import { streamText, convertToModelMessages, UIMessage } from 'ai';
import { run } from '../../lib/run';

const tools = {
  web_fetch: anthropic.tools.webFetch_20250910({ maxUses: 5 }),
};

run(async () => {
  // Step 1: trigger a web_fetch error
  const result1 = streamText({
    model: anthropic('claude-sonnet-4-20250514'),
    tools,
    system: 'Always use web_fetch when asked to fetch a URL.',
    messages: [
      {
        role: 'user',
        content: 'Please fetch the content from http://localhost:9999/secret',
      },
    ],
  });

  let assistantMessage: UIMessage | undefined;

  const stream = result1.toUIMessageStream({
    onError: () => 'Oops, an error occurred!',
    onFinish: async ({ messages }) => {
      assistantMessage = messages.at(-1);
    },
  });

  for await (const _ of stream) {
  }

  // Step 2: simulate DB round-trip (save then reload)
  const persisted: UIMessage = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(assistantMessage!));

  for (const part of persisted.parts) {
    if ((part as any).state === 'output-error') {
      console.log('errorText after persistence:', (part as any).errorText);
    }
  }

  // Step 3: send follow-up with persisted messages
  const followUpMessages: UIMessage[] = [
    {
      id: '1',
      role: 'user',
      parts: [{ type: 'text', text: 'Fetch http://localhost:9999/secret' }],
    },
    persisted,
    {
      id: '2',
      role: 'user',
      parts: [{ type: 'text', text: 'What happened?' }],
    },
  ];

  const modelMessages = await convertToModelMessages(followUpMessages);

  const result2 = streamText({
    model: anthropic('claude-sonnet-4-20250514'),
    tools,
    messages: modelMessages,
  });

  const text = await result2.text;
  console.log('Follow-up response:', text);
});

```
</details>

